Name: Hinkler
Description:
The Division of Hinkler consists of:

  • part of the Bundaberg Regional Council, and
  • part of the Fraser Coast Regional Council.
ProductsAndIndustry: Sugar, a myriad of small crops including tomatoes, avocados and macadamia nuts, rum, fishing, seafood industries and tourism.
NameDerivation: Named in honour of Herbert John (Bert) Hinkler DSM AFC, 1892-1933, aviator who was the first person to fly solo from England to Australia in 1928.

DemographicRating: Provincial - outside capital cities, but with a majority of enrolment in major provincial cities
